  "instruction": "From the compact grouped anomaly summary generated earlier (use the kernel-stored anomaly groups), filter to keep only groups that indicate a meaningful high-sided breach during the window. Specifically:\n1) Keep groups where p95 > 0 AND severity_pct = (max_value - p95) / p95 > 0.5 (i.e., the max in-window value exceeds p95 by more than 50%).\n2) For each kept group produce columns: component, kpi_name, anomaly_count_in_window, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, max_value_in_window, p50, p95, severity_pct. Sort by severity_pct descending then anomaly_count_in_window descending and return top 20 rows.\n3) Also return a compact per-component summary (component, number_of_severe_groups) sorted by number_of_severe_groups desc.\n4) Store the full filtered group table in the kernel variable filtered_anoms_severe but only print the requested compact tables (top 20 and per-component counts)."
