  "instruction": "Using trace_anoms_window (the kernel-stored anomaly rows within the window) joined to the trace_aggr P50/P95 thresholds, produce a compact table of TRACE-SEVERE records filtered by severity_pct > 0.5 and anomaly_type == 'high'. For each record include columns: component (cmdb_id), trace_name, anomaly_count_in_window, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, max_value_in_window, p50, p95, severity_pct. Sort by severity_pct descending, then anomaly_count_in_window descending, limit to top 20 rows. Also return: (a) count of unique components among these filtered trace severe records, and (b) list of top 10 distinct trace_name patterns (with counts). Store the full filtered trace severe details in kernel variable trace_severe_details but only print the requested compact table and the two summary numbers/lists."
