    "analysis": "We have followed the preprocess -> anomaly detection -> trace analysis steps. Global thresholds (P50/P95/P99) were computed from full-series aggregations. Windowed anomalies (2021-03-24 16:30–17:00 UTC+8) were detected and filtered to 'severe' groups where in-window max exceeds P95 by >50%. The severe-group aggregates show the heaviest concentration of severe anomalies on MG02 and MG01 (30 and 28 severe KPI groups respectively), followed by Tomcat nodes (Tomcat04/03/02). Trace analysis of severe trace anomalies shows very large latency spikes in traces involving dockerA2, dockerA1, MG01 and MG02 (e.g., dockerA2 trace.self.duration_p95 with severity_pct ≈ 59x, and many trace.to_/from_ duration spikes where MG01/MG02↔dockerA* durations exceed p95 by multiple times). According to the localization rules, multiple components at the same level are faulty and traces suggest the MG nodes and dockerA containers are in the slow call chains; we should now confirm resource-level reasons by inspecting metric KPIs for the top candidate components (MG01 and MG02) in the incident window to identify whether the root cause is high CPU, memory, disk, network, or JVM-related. Logs can be used afterward if metrics point to multiple possible reasons.",
