  "instruction": "From the kernel-stored metric_anoms_window (anomaly rows within the window), filter to component in {MG01, MG02}. For these rows, join to metric_aggr to get p50 and p95 (already computed). Produce a compact grouped summary (limit 20 rows) grouped by (component, kpi_name) with columns: component, kpi_name, anomaly_count_in_window, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, max_value_in_window, p50, p95, severity_pct = (max_value_in_window - p95)/p95. Sort by severity_pct descending then anomaly_count_in_window descending. Also return: (a) a small per-component summary showing counts of distinct severe KPIs for MG01 and MG02, and (b) list of top 10 kpi_name patterns (with counts) among these MG01/MG02 metric anomalies. Store the full filtered rows in the kernel variable mg_metric_anoms but only print the requested compact summary table and the two small lists/counts."
}

